## Advantages Over Cable-Tendon Systems

| Property | Cable-Tendon | This System |
|----------|-------------|-------------|
| Force control | Torque limited, binary | Analogue, continuous |
| Load sensing | Requires external sensors | Inherent to circuit |
| Compliance | Fixed | Variable in real time |
| Failure mode | Catastrophic (cable snap) | Graceful (slow leak) |
| Packaging density | High (cables + sensors + wiring) | Low (sealed circuits) |
| Redundancy | Physically impossible at scale | Parallel circuits possible |
| DOF potential | Limited by cable routing space | Higher — cleaner packaging |

---

## Advantages Over Pneumatic Systems

- Incompressible fluid = precise positional control (pneumatics are compressible)
- Sealed system = one small leak is manageable, not system failure
- Variable compliance without external regulators
- No compressor required

---

## Application Examples

### Humanoid Robotics
- Full human DOF hand (27+) with precise variable force at every joint
- Forearm packaging dramatically simplified vs cable routing
- Marshmallow-to-steel-bar grip range in same hand
- Tactile feedback without fingertip sensor arrays

### Industrial Robotics
- Assembly lines handling mixed fragile/rigid components
- No retooling between product types — compliance adjusted in software
- Reduced maintenance vs cable systems (no stretch, no wear)
- Sealed against dust, coolant, industrial contamination

### Medical / Surgical Robotics
- Sub-millimetre force control for tissue handling
- Pressure feedback replaces surgeon's tactile sense in remote procedures
- Sealed circuits — sterilisation compatible
- Graceful degradation — no sudden loss of control

### Prosthetics
- Natural compliance matching human grip feel
- Load feedback enables object recognition by feel
- Variable stiffness for different daily tasks
- Lightweight sealed system — wearable long term

### Heavy Industry / Exoskeletons
- Scale the fluid viscosity and chamber size for heavy load applications
- Same control architecture, different fluid spec
- Force amplification with retained tactile feedback
- Worker fatigue reduction with maintained precision

